alysis Create TAB 5: Dependencies Matrix for cross-referencing and sequence planning Add conditional formatting for priority levels and status colors Add sample data entries to demonstrate the system Fix Priority Score formula to use weighted calculation (35% monetization, 25% ease, 40% impact) The comprehensive content workflow automation system is now complete. Here's a summary of what was built: ✅ Content Workflow Automation System - Complete 5-Tab Structure Created: Tab\tPurpose\tKey Features Master Content Tracker\tCentral hub for 100+ content ideas\t17 columns, weighted priority scoring, conditional formatting, 15 sample entries Platform Integration Hub\tTrack share links across platforms\tAuto-lookup titles, Confluence/Docmost/GitBook pre-configured Automation Workflows\tDefine triggers & actions\t7 workflow templates for publishing, syncing, alerts, cleanup Category Performance\tDashboard analytics\tCOUNTIF/AVERAGEIF formulas, completion rates, category breakdowns Dependencies Matrix\tSequence planning\tCross-reference dependencies, risk levels, blocking status Key Automation Features: Weighted Priority Score: (Monetization × 35%) + (Setup Ease × 25%) + (Immediate Impact × 40%) Auto-Ranking: Items automatically ranked 1-150 based on priority score Conditional Formatting: 🟢 Green = High Priority (8-10) 🟡 Yellow = Medium Priority (5-7.99) 🔴 Red = Low Priority (<5) Status colors for Published/In Progress/Review/Idea/Archived Cross-Sheet Lookups: Platform Integration & Dependencies Matrix auto-pull titles from Master Tracker Dashboard Formulas: Real-time category stats, completion rates, averages 7 Pre-Built Workflow Templates: Confluence Auto-Publish - On status change → Convert MD→HTML → Upload → Get share link Docmost Sync - Hourly → Format → Push to API → Log link GitBook Update - On content modify → Commit → Build → Update link Priority Alert - Real-time → Notify when Priority > 8 → Add to backlog Weekly Report - Monday 9 AM → Generate stats → Email stakeholders Dependency Check - Before publish → Validate links → Approve/block Archive Cleanup - Monthly → Backup → Remove from platforms Next Steps to Implement: Add your 100+ content ideas to the Master Content Tracker (rows 17+) Link share URLs in Platform Integration Hub as you publish Map dependencies in Dependencies Matrix for sequencing Connect to automation tools (Zapier/Make/n8n) using the workflow definitions Monitor Category Performance dashboard for ROI insights Content Workflow Automation Tracker Task completed: sheets_new View Result Using Tool | Infographic Answer Content Workflow Automation System 5 points professional Nano Banana Pro Remix Image Image to Video CONTENT WORKFLOW AUTOMATION: TACTICAL TASK LIST 🎯 IMMEDIATE ACTION ITEMS PHASE 1: SPREADSHEET SETUP Task\tAction\tExpected Input\tExpected Output\tTime Access Master Sheet\tOpen Content Tracker\tBrowser access\t5-tab automated system\t2 min Import Content Ideas\tAdd 100+ ideas to Master Content Tracker\tTitle, description, category, scores (1-10)\tAuto-calculated priority rankings\t30 min Configure Platforms\tSet platform URLs in Integration Hub\tConfluence, Docmost, GitBook base URLs\tReady-to-use publishing tracker\t10 min PHASE 2: AUTOMATION SETUP Automation Tool\tWorkflow\tTrigger\tAction\tImplementation Zapier/Make\tConfluence Auto-Publish\tStatus → \"Ready\"\tConvert MD→HTML, upload, get link\tConnect to sheet API GitHub Actions\tGitBook Sync\tFile commit\tAuto-build, deploy, update share link\tYAML workflow file Platform APIs\tDocmost Integration\tScheduled hourly\tBatch upload, collect URLs\tAPI key + webhook Google Scripts\tPriority Alerts\tReal-time\tEmail when Priority Score >8\tTrigger on edit PHASE 3: CONTENT CATEGORIZATION Category\tTag Examples\tMonetization Priority\tSetup Ease\tImpact Score Product Guides\ttutorial, onboarding\t8-9\t6-7\t9-10 Sales Funnels\tconversion, lead-gen\t9-10\t4-6\t8-9 Course Content\teducation, premium\t9-10\t7-8\t7-8 Blog/SEO\ttraffic, organic\t6-7\t8-9\t6-7 Documentation\ttechnical, support\t4-5\t9-10\t8-9 🔄 AUTOMATION WORKFLOWS (PRE-BUILT) WORKFLOW 1: CONFLUENCE AUTO-PUBLISH Copy Trigger: Master Sheet Status = \"Ready to Publish\" Actions: 1. Convert .md to HTML via Pandoc API 2. Upload to Confluence via REST API 3. Extract share link 4. Update Platform Integration Hub 5. Set status to \"Published\" WORKFLOW 2: DEPENDENCY VALIDATION Copy Trigger: Before any publish action Actions: 1. Check Dependencies Matrix 2. Validate all prerequisite content exists 3. Block/approve based on dependency status 4. Alert if blocking issues found WORKFLOW 3: PERFORMANCE TRACKING Copy Trigger: Weekly (Mondays 9 AM) Actions: 1. Calculate category completion rates 2. Generate ROI analysis from Category Dashboard 3. Email stakeholder report 4. Update priority rankings based on performance 📊 RANKING SYSTEM (AUTOMATED) Priority Score Formula: Monetization Impact: 35% (Direct revenue potential) Setup Ease: 25% (Implementation speed) Immediate Impact: 40% (Business goal advancement) Auto-Ranking Tiers: 🟢 High Priority (8.0-10.0): Immediate action required 🟡 Medium Priority (5.0-7.9): Schedule within 30 days 🔴 Low Priority (<5.0): Backlog for future consideration 🎛️ NEXT STEPS CHECKLIST Access spreadsheet and populate first 20 content ideas Configure platform API keys for Confluence/Docmost/GitBook Set up Zapier/Make connections using provided workflow templates Map dependencies for top 10 priority items Enable email alerts for high-priority content identification Schedule weekly reviews of Category Performance Dashboard SYSTEM READY TO DEPLOY → Start with Phase 1, then activate automations progressively as content volume increases. Super Agent Your first AI employee Free Today +13 Ultra Speak"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=fabb0a2f-3273-4d44-ba87-317846b81893","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=fabb0a2f-3273-4d44-ba87-317846b81893"}]}]}]
